Class RemoteList<T extends RemoteObject>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractList<T>
        • ca.ualberta.cs.wrkify.RemoteList<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the remote object that the list is of.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>, java.util.Collection<T>, java.util.List<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    RemoteQueryList

    public class RemoteList<T extends RemoteObject>
extends java.util.AbstractList<T>
    RemoteList is a List of Remote objects that can be refreshed. It internally stores the objects as well and gets them as needed. this type should NOT be serialized.
    See Also:
    RemoteClient, RemoteObject, List
